review_blob: Pour pitch black with a frothy head. Rich note of roasted malt mixed with a hint of hop in aroma. Smooth, lingering mid bitterness finish. A well balanced stout if not a bit too light.

Mystic golden amber body with thin white head. Lingering lacing on the glass. Very well balanced IPA with an orangy nose and a hint of malt in the back end. Smooooooth palate and finish. The hop never dominates the taste but it makes its presence felt. A surprisingly full body IPA which cant be said to other noteworthy IPAs from Bells or Laguitas. highly recommended. Worth the price of admission.
Medium white head with opaque mystic golden body. Full body for an IPA. Smooth palate.
Huge thick white head on top of the amber gold body. A beauty in the glass. Big hop/malt aroma coming through the nose. The palate is much the same. A hop monster in the can. Can you handle it?
beer_name: Oskar Blues Deviant Dales India Pale Ale

review_blob: Huge foamy white head with Golden body. Strong banana peel and yeast aroma. Surprisingly bitter for this type of beer.
Very smooth on the palate. Great malty nose and mouth feeling. Nutty and good weight on the palate.
Have all the characteristics of a brew coming out of Lagunitas. Extremely hoppy, golden body but with very little head.  Very floral, stickiness on the palate.
UPDATED: SEP 20, 2013
Toffee caramel nose with a hint of hop in the mix. Opaque black with good amount of carbonated head. Fairly light body for a stout. Middle of the road, half-hearted attempt. Not impressed.
UPDATED: JAN 27, 2013

A very floral IPA. Strong aroma of hop, grapefruit and malt. Tastes much the same as the nose. Clean palate and pleasant finish. Great malt mixture. Not bitter or overdone like its name suggests. A very enjoyable IPA.

Dark Mahogany pour. No head, no lace. Strong aroma of hop, citrus and malt. Fresh and light on the palate. Hop, grapefruit, and malt taste. A great drink especially served cold. I am just surprised it didnt the weight or boldness I was expected.
UPDATED: AUG 11, 2012
Pour dark mahogany color with no head. Aroma of malt. Taste of sweet malt and caramel. Thick palate and long-lasting smooth finish.

Pitch black with thin brown head. Caramel nose with a slight hint of dark chocolate. Roasty chocolate, medium body, smooth finish. The 8.3% alcohol did not come through at all. Good balance. Good stout.
Highly carbonated. Taste like Pilner on steroid. A good hot summer night drink. Yeasty with banana peel. Not bad, but not worth the premium.
UPDATED: JUN 5, 2012
UPDATED: SEP 7, 2012
UPDATED: JUN 20, 2012
Misty golden pour, thin bubbly head. A bit dry on the palate but very pleasant. Great to enjoy in summer. Overall, a hop-forward but balanced IPA. Not overpowering, not overly bitter.
Reminds me a lot about Laguitas Maximus. Hop, malt interplay. Very tasty and well-crafted. It is priced a bit high ($4 a bottle), so that might be the reason why I wouldnt get it again.
UPDATED: JUL 5, 2013
Amber copper body, no head. Banana-peel nose. Malt, yeast...I taste a bit of scotch on the palate. Intriguing!
Pours copper gold with no head. Soft lacing. Malt, hop, citrus nose and taste. Slightly muddy palate. Typical IPA finish, bitter, too bitter for me.. Reminds me a lot of Laguitas IPA.

This porter lives up to its "robust" claim. it tastes more like a stout than a porter. 

Toasted coffee head on top of brownish black body. Lots of lacing on the glass. Impressive roasted coffee, malt, dark chocolate aroma with hop. More hop than most porters. Again roasted coffee, malt, dark chocolate taste and medium weight. Smooth, creamy finish.
UPDATED: MAY 6, 2012
Lots of banana-peel nose and taste. Carbonated white head. Very impressed with the quality of  this supposedly-commercially-available beer.

Sweet Orange-peel, yeasty, wheaty nose. Tangerine gold with huge thick white head. Good amount of carbonation. Smooth, creamy palate dominated by tropical fruit, orange, pineapple and hint of citrus. A pleasant, sweet, hot summer night type of beverage.
UPDATED: AUG 12, 2012
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Sumpin Ale
